<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12944:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-09T00:00:00+02:00">July
                                        9, 1941—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received July 9—8:25
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2920. For the President and Acting Secretary.<note n="55" xml:id="d194fn55">Sumner Welles.</note> My 2911, July 9, 8
                                    p.m.<note n="56" xml:id="d194fn56">Not printed.</note> Mr. Eden
                                has informed me the Cabinet agreed this evening to conclusion of
                                agreement with Russia in form of joint declaration. Sir Stafford
                                Cripps has been so advised but formal proposal to Stalin cannot be
                                made until after consultation with Dominions’ Governments which is
                                being done by cable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>